definition: to take in and send out (in large quantities)
to spit/to send out (silk from a silkworm, bolls from cotton flowers etc)/to say/to pour out (one's grievances)
to hum and haw (idiom); to mumble as if hiding sth/to speak and break off, then start again/to hold sth back

sentences.english: Event throughput is bound by the server speed.
sentences.chinese: 事件吞吐量受服务器的速度限制。

sentences.english: He hesitated and added, the muscles of his face contracting whitely.
sentences.chinese: 他一脸的肌肉在皱缩发白，一面吞吞吐吐地接下去说。
